An absolute path is the complete path from the root directory (/) to a file or directory.
	Always starts with /
	Independent of the current directory
	Gives the full location
/home/student/Documents/Linux/notes.txt
*
A relative path specifies the location of a file or directory relative to the current working directory.
	Does NOT start with /
	Depends on where you are currently
	Shorter and easier for quick navigation
If current directory is:
/home/student
Relative path:
Documents/Linux/notes.txt
 Symbol	Meaning
 .	Current directory
 ..	Parent directory
 ~	Home directory
